+-- | Rebuild a guarded formula bottom-up with the 'gconj' smart
+-- constructor, restoring the normal form that 'formulaToGuarded'
+-- establishes (flattened, duplicate-free conjunctions/disjunctions).
+-- Substitution can break this normal form — e.g. two conjuncts become
+-- syntactically identical once @$B@ is instantiated to @$A@ — after which
+-- the printed form of a stored goal is no longer round-trippable: parsing
+-- re-normalises, so the re-parsed goal fails the exact-equality lookup
+-- during proof replay ("invalid proof step encountered").
+-- NOTE: disjunctions are normalised CONSTRUCTOR-PRESERVING at every
+-- level ('normaliseDisj'), not via the full 'gdisj': a singleton
+-- disjunction wrapping a conjunction (created mid-solve by disjunct
+-- pruning) is load-bearing for the S_∀ saturation dedup — 'insertFormula'
+-- STORES disjunctions (formula + DisjG goal twin) but DECOMPOSES bare
+-- conjunctions without storing them, so unwrapping the singleton turns a
+-- storable, dedupable derived instance into one that re-fires on every
+-- simplifier iteration (livelock on ake/bilinear/TAK1_eCK_like.spthy).
+-- Conjunctions use the full 'gconj' (their singleton unwrap is harmless
+-- precisely because conjunctions are decomposed on insertion anyway);
+-- this requires 'gconj' to be idempotent — see the note on 'gconj'.
+normaliseGuarded :: (Ord s, Ord c, Ord v) => Guarded s c v -> Guarded s c v
+normaliseGuarded = foldGuarded GAto (GDisj . normaliseDisj) (gconj . getConj) GGuarded
+
+-- | Flatten nested disjunctions and drop duplicate disjuncts WITHOUT
+-- changing the constructor: no singleton unwrap and no truth-value
+-- absorption happen, so a @GDisj@ formula and its @DisjG@ goal twin
+-- (which share the @Disj@ payload but wrap it differently) stay in
+-- LOCKSTEP under this transformation.  Using the full 'gdisj' here
+-- instead would dedup the formula twin's list while a per-element map on
+-- the goal twin's 'Disj' container keeps duplicates — exactly the
+-- identity split that makes 'markGoalAsSolved' miss its key (observed as
+-- non-termination on @csf19-wrapping/gcm.spthy@).
